A single dark, vertically-elongated humeral blotch, with dorsal portion wider, extending over three to four horizontal series of scales above the lateral line and two below. Portion of humeral blotch located dorsal to lateral line sometimes interrupted vertically by narrow clear stripe. Region immediately anterior and posterior to humeral blotch pale. Body with an inconspicuous grey midlateral stripe, extending from two to three scales on the rear of the humeral blotch to tip of caudal-fin rays, lighter in some specimens at posterior region of caudal peduncle and- or caudal-fin base. Chromatophores concentrated on posterior border of body scales, imparting a reticulate pattern. Scattered dark chromatophores widespread between lateral line and base of anal fin. Adipose fin beige, with few scattered dark chromatophores. Remaining fins with scattered chromatophores homogeneously distributed along the interradial membranes and edges of the rays (
Fig. 1
).
